<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 30 at 2:15AM MDT until July 30 at 3:00AM MDT by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>The National Weather Service in Glasgow has issued a
* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Daniels County in northeastern Montana...
Northwestern Roosevelt County in northeastern Montana...
Northeastern Valley County in northeastern Montana...
* Until 300 AM MDT.
* At 214 AM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 17 miles north of
St. Marie, or 17 miles southwest of Opheim, moving southeast at 35
mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
* Locations impacted include...
Opheim, Tampico, St. Marie, Baylor, Glentana and Larslan.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
